      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates QoI change <2% between medium and fine mesh.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on representative screw-rod construct. Stiffness QoI changed 1.1% between medium (element edge length 0.5 mm) and fine (0.25 mm) mesh. Medium mesh adopted for production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver residuals monitored; iterative convergence confirmed for each load step.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear static analysis with arc-length control. Force and displacement residuals converged to 1e-4 relative tolerance at each load step. No divergence events observed across 11 model instances."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup and boundary conditions by analyst not involved in original model construction.",
      "rationale": "Model inputs, boundary conditions, and post-processing scripts reviewed by a second FDA analyst. Three minor errors in constraint definitions corrected prior to final runs. Corrected model re-verified against benchmark."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum FEA with elastic-plastic material model and frictional contact is appropriate for ASTM F1717 quasi-static compression-bending.",
      "rationale": "Isotropic elastic-plastic (bilinear kinematic hardening) material model for Ti-6Al-4V screw and rod. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) at screw-rod interface. Model form consistent with published literature for metallic implant compression-bending analysis. Simplifications (no bone block deformation, rigid polyacetal blocks) consistent with ASTM F1717 test configuration."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric dimensions sourced from certified material test reports and dimensional inspection data for each of the 11 test specimens.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (114 GPa), yield strength (880 MPa), and tangent modulus (1.8 GPa) from lot-specific tensile test certificates. Screw and rod geometry from CMM measurements on production hardware. Dimensional variability across N=11 specimens incorporated as model input uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test specimens from production lots; specimens representative of intended commercial design.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested (6 at Lab 1, 5 at Lab 2). All specimens from production lots released under DePuy Synthes QMS. Dimensional inspection confirmed conformance to engineering drawings. Inter-laboratory variability assessed; no statistically significant difference in mean stiffness (p=0.31)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios including at least two load levels.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single displacement rate (5 mm/min) and single construct geometry per ASTM F1717. Only one load condition (compression-bending to 40 mm) evaluated. This factor achieves Gradation 2 rather than the required Gradation 3 because no parametric variation in load level or construct geometry was included. This shortfall is documented and accepted given that ASTM F1717 is a standardized pass/fail test with a single prescribed condition."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions and loading match experimental test configuration to within documented tolerances.",
      "rationale": "FEA boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 fixture geometry: rigid polyacetal block constraints, 40 mm inter-block spacing, axial compressive load applied at 5° offset per standard. Load application point and constraint locations confirmed against laboratory fixture drawings. Friction coefficient sensitivity study performed; QoI insensitive to mu in range 0.15–0.25."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (percent difference and E/uval) computed for each QoI; all within pre-established acceptance bounds.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs compared: construct stiffness (4.3%, E/uval=0.87), yield force (6.1%, E/uval=1.12), force at 40 mm (7.8%, E/uval=1.54). All within pre-established bounds of <10% and E/uval<1.96. Validation uncertainty (uval) computed from experimental standard deviation and model input uncertainty using RSS method."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly correspond to regulatory submission metrics and clinical failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in the FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions and directly correspond to construct fatigue and fracture risk metrics. QoI selection reviewed and approved by FDA project team prior to study initiation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario (ASTM F1717 bench test) is the same scenario as the COU; no extrapolation required.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity is identical to the COU: ASTM F1717 static compression-bending of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. No geometric, material, or loading extrapolation is required. The validation directly supports the regulatory submission claim."
    }
  ],
